        "title": "feat(init): detect repo checks during onboarding",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add opt-in `crabbox init --detect` for generating a `jobs.detected` remote check\n- detect Go modules, Node package scripts, Rust crates, and root Makefile test targets\n- add lockfile-aware package-manager commands, preflight tools, docs, and tests\n\n## Verification\n- `go test ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `npm run docs:check`\n- `git diff --check`\n- runtime smoke of `crabbox init --detect` on a temp Go + Node repo\n\n## Runtime proof\nBuilt the current branch CLI and ran `crabbox init --detect` inside a temp repo containing `go.mod`, root `package.json`, and a locked nested `worker/package.json`.\n\n```text\nwrote /tmp/crabbox-detect-proof.ndRpUP/.crabbox.yaml\nwrote /tmp/crabbox-detect-proof.ndRpUP/.github/workflows/crabbox.yml\nwrote /tmp/crabbox-detect-proof.ndRpUP/.agents/skills/crabbox/SKILL.md\ndetected job: crabbox job run detected\n```\n\nGenerated `.crabbox.yaml` excerpt:\n\n```yaml\nrun:\n  preflightTools:\n    - go\n    - node\n    - npm\njobs:\n  detected:\n    shell: true\n    command: >\n      go test ./... &&\n      npm install && npm run 'check' &&\n      npm --prefix 'worker' ci && npm --prefix 'worker' test\n    stop: auto\n```",
